                <h3>A home and hope</h3>
                <div class="news-subheader mb-4">Your contributions have given Wu Xueli a second chance</div>
                <img class="img-fluid story-img" src="~/images/news/issue9/story-1.jpg">
                <figcaption class="figure-caption caption">Thanks to your contributions, Wu Xueli has a new purpose: to live his life positively.</figcaption>
                <p class="clear">Moving the Renewal Center to a new location has been great. But in the shuffle and set up, we unfortunately lost touch with one of our residential job program trainees, Wu Xueli.</p>
                <p>After meeting him, I knew Wu Xueli would truly benefit from learning job skills in our communal setting. He was quiet but eager to learn and was always willing to work hard in the cafe. So, I was heartbroken when he disappeared in the craziness of our move.</p>
                <p>Thankfully, I have good news! Your gifts gave us the resources to search for Wu Xueli. It took a few months, but we found him and he rejoined our residency program.</p>
                <p>This opportunity has been life changing for Wu Xueli. He first came to Shanghai to see the lights of the city, but he ended up living on the streets and was too ashamed to return to his home in Chongqing.</p>
                <p>“I slept in the waiting hall of the railway station and ferry terminal. In the daytime, I would pick up bottles, help assemble temporary stages or any other work I could find,” said Wu Xueli.</p>
                <blockquote>
                    Before I was in the dust, but now I am over the sky.<br><italic>-Wu Xueli</italic>
                </blockquote>
                <p>He came to the center after a homeless friend told him he could get a free meal, a shower, and do his laundry here. Since joining the job program, he’s gotten so much more than that.</p>
                <p>“Before I was like the dust, but now I am over the sky,” he said. “I am very happy because this center and the concepts here have helped me a lot.”</p>
                <p>Now our friend is building confidence and working towards independence. Wu Xueli has you to thank for that. Because of your support, he has found a home and hope in Shanghai.</p>
                <p>“I will live my life positively,” he said.</p>
            </div>
