            <div id="story-2">
                <h2>Renewal is happening in Shanghai</h2>
                <div class="news-subheader">We are helping the marginalized and forgotten thanks to your support</div>
                <p class="mb4"><em>Jimmy McWhinney Executive Director Hanson Ye Operations Director</em></p>
                <p class="clear">Great things are unfolding at the Renewal Center! We just celebrated our first full year in our new location. It’s been a whirlwind filled with new guests, returning friends and great successes.</p>
                <p>As you may remember, we asked for help to purchase a van in our last newsletter. Through many generous gifts, we were able to order it. The new vehicle will allow us to provide a shuttle service from the city center to our drop-in center, meeting a need for our most vulnerable elderly and disabled guests. It’s thanks to your generosity that we could extend this service to a population that is often forgotten in Shanghai.</p>
                <p>We’ve also been able to reconnect with old friends like Wu Xueli (page 1) and ramp up our residential job training program (opposite page). Thank you for being a part of this exciting and life-giving work. It truly makes a difference in so many lives.</p>         
            </div>
